        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Historical note</head>
            <p>The Saint Ambrose School was a Catholic school located on the west side of Tompkins Avenue, between DeKalb Avenue and Kosciuszko Street, in the Bedford-Stuyvesant neighborhood of Brooklyn, New York. According to the website Forgotten New York, "[the church was] constructed in 1883, the school 1911. The Catholic church and school closed in 1978, merging with Our Lady of Monserrate on nearby Vernon Avenue."</p>
            <p>The alumni of Saint Ambrose School maintain a 
                <extref ns2:href="http://www.stambroseschool.us/">website</extref> with information on the school at 
                <extref ns2:href="http://www.stambroseschool.us/">http://www.stambroseschool.us/</extref>.</p>
            <p>Sources:</p>
            <p>Kevin Walsh, "WILLIAMSBURG to BEDFORD-STUYVESANT, Brooklyn," 
                <emph render="italic">Forgotten New York</emph>, accessed September 5, 2015, 
                <extref ns2:href="http://forgotten-ny.com/2011/01/williamsburg-to-bedford-stuyvesant-brooklyn/">http://forgotten-ny.com/2011/01/williamsburg-to-bedford-stuyvesant-brooklyn/</extref></p>
        </bioghist>
